define({"topics":[{"title":"Minimum viable docset","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Minimum viable documentation set (MVD) is the smallest amount of documentation needed so that the majority of developers willingly adopt an API, just enough that they don't feel overwhelmed by frustration or give up because the API wastes their time.<\/p>","href":"topics\/minimum-viable-docset_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"minimum-viable-documentation-for-apis"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"minimum-viable-documentation-for-apis-d282e136","topics":[]},{"title":"Complete the MVD project","href":"topics\/completing-mvd_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"the-process-for-completing-your-mvd-project"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"the-process-for-completing-your-mvd-project-d282e145","topics":[]},{"title":"API reference","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The largest and most important part of the reference documentation is the section that describes all of the API endpoints.<\/p>","href":"topics\/basic-reference.html","attributes":{"data-id":"the-api-reference-docs-are-yours-complete"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"the-api-reference-docs-are-yours-complete-d282e151","topics":[]},{"title":"API reference example","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The following is a reference entry for one endpoint on a fictional API. This is just one way to represent all the necessary information.<\/p>","href":"topics\/reference-example-container.html","attributes":{"data-id":"example-reference-entry"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"example-reference-entry-d282e160","topics":[]},{"title":"Working with OAS3 and Swagger","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">It's easy to assume that the OAS3 spec results in documentation with more accuracy or completeness compared to documentation that isn't programmatically generated. Not necessarily. The spec is ultimately written by humans, and information can be missing or incorrect.<\/p>","href":"topics\/swagger-reference_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"whats-missing-from-your-swagger-docs-how-to-ensure-completeness-when-working-with-openapi-3"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"whats-missing-from-your-swagger-docs-how-to-ensure-completeness-when-working-with-openapi-3-d282e169","topics":[]},{"title":"Writing the overview","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If the project is brand new or hasn't had a technical writer before, it most likely lacks an overview. You should write one.<\/p>","href":"topics\/non-reference-overview_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"non-reference-documentation-writing-the-overview"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"non-reference-documentation-writing-the-overview-d282e178","topics":[]},{"title":"Writing the quickstart","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">A quickstart helps new users get through their first experience using software.<\/p>","href":"topics\/non-reference-quickstart_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"the-quickstart"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"the-quickstart-d282e187","topics":[]},{"title":"Beyond MVD","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you have sized up your API and written all the docs you need for MVD, you have come a long way, but there's more. (Like software, documentation is never done.)<\/p>","href":"topics\/beyond-mvd_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"beyond-mvd-expanding-your-documentation-as-the-product-matures"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"beyond-mvd-expanding-your-documentation-as-the-product-matures-d282e196","topics":[]},{"title":"The how-to article","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">A how-to article is a set of steps that describe how to accomplish one particular goal.<\/p>","href":"topics\/how-to_2.html","menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"tocId-d282e205","topics":[]}]});